The U.S. airline industry is ramping up cost-cutting efforts to deal with
skyrocketing fuel prices.  Nearly all the major U.S. carriers have announced
major job cuts this year.  But airline representatives say cutting jobs is not
enough.  They're asking lawmakers to do more to reduce fuel costs that now
threaten the US airline industry.  VOA's Mil Arcega has more.

 
 
 
 
